"version": "1.0.4",
"title": "8201: blamelessness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8201",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A quality of life apparent in an individual against whom no just charge can be made. This is exemplified supremely in the blameless life and death of Jesus Christ. Though believers remain imperfect in this life, they are counted blameless in God's sight on account of the atoning death of Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's human life was blameless</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:22\">1PE 2:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:9\">ISA 53:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:46\">JHN 8:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:21\">2CO 5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:26\">HEB 7:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:19\">1PE 1:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:5\">1JN 3:5</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's blameless life and death were the perfect fulfilment of the OT sacrifices</h2>\n<h3>The lamb or goat sacrificed at Passover had to be unblemished</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:5\">EXO 12:5</a></strong></p>\n<h3>All other animals used as sacrifices had to be without defect</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev1:3\">LEV 1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:6\">LEV 6:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:14\">NUM 6:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:19\">NUM 28:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:21\">DEU 15:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:23\">EZK 45:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:8\">MAL 1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:13-Mal1:14\">MAL 1:13–1:14</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's death was as the perfect lamb of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:14\">HEB 9:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:29\">JHN 1:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:7\">1CO 5:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:19\">1PE 1:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:6\">REV 5:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:1\">REV 6:1</a></p>\n<h2>In the OT, the righteous were often described as blameless</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:9\">GEN 6:9</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:1\">JOB 1:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:3\">1SA 12:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:21-2Sam22:25\">2SA 22:21–22:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps15:1-Ps15:5\">PSA 15:1–15:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:37\">PSA 37:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:20\">PRO 11:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:18\">PRO 28:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:7\">SNG 4:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:6\">LUK 1:6</a></p>\n<h2>God counts believers as blameless in his sight on account of Jesus Christ's death for them</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:39\">ACT 13:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:28\">ROM 3:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:1\">ROM 5:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:11\">1CO 6:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:6\">GAL 3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:4\">EPH 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:9\">PHP 3:9</a></p>\n<h2>Believers should be blameless in their Christian lives</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:7\">1TI 5:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:3\">2CO 6:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:10\">PHP 1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:14-Phil2:15\">PHP 2:14–2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:15\">1PE 1:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:12\">1PE 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:14\">2PE 3:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:27\">JAS 1:27</a></p>\n<h3>Paul, Silas and Timothy could claim to have been blameless</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:10\">1TH 2:10</a></p>\n<h3>Officers of the church are to be blameless</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:2\">1TI 3:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:14\">1TI 6:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:6-Titus1:7\">TIT 1:6–1:7</a></p>\n<h3>The administration of financial help is to be blameless</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:20\">2CO 8:20</a></p>\n<h2>Believers will be presented blameless before God at the last day</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:8\">1CO 1:8</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:24\">JUD 1:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:27\">EPH 5:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:22\">COL 1:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess3:13\">1TH 3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:23\">1TH 5:23</a></p>",
